A lightweight, TOML-backed configuration/settings utility that that exposes project settings as standard Python dictionaries.

mooch-settings is a Python configuration library designed for simplicity and developer ergonomics. It loads settings data from TOML files and exposes them as standard Python dictionaries ‚Äî allowing you to work with settings in a familiar, Pythonic way.

